						<summary>

						<p>The king is given the attribute “who was pleased to take Madurai”. This also records a similar gift of 6 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land after reclamation by payment of money by Vaṇṇaṉ Maṉṟuḷḷāḍuvāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śembiyaṉ Pallavaraiyaṉ of Puduvūr in Ārvalakkūṟṟam, a division of Rājēndraśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu, for burning a lamp in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
